{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1772048170,"nonce":"Pidhm21pKh5pQqcCYrHsRzCQNZg=","message":"[GitHub comment by i-m-mll on 2026-01-26T17:20:20Z]\n\n## Clarification: Use Penzai selectors vs. re-implement\n\nThe original issue frames this as implementing a custom selector system. However, **Penzai's selectors work on any PyTree**, not just Penzai model objects. The `.select()` method on `pz.Struct` is just a convenience; `pz.select(tree)` works on Equinox modules, plain dicts, or any JAX-registered PyTree.\n\n### Option A: Use Penzai selectors directly\n\n```python\nimport penzai as pz\n\n# Works on any Equinox module\nselection = pz.select(feedbax_model).at_instances_of(eqx.nn.Linear)\nmodified = selection.apply(lambda layer: ...)\n```\n\n**Pros**:\n- Zero implementation effort\n- Battle-tested, full feature set\n- Maintained by DeepMind\n\n**Cons**:\n- Adds `penzai` as a dependency (though only `penzai.core.selectors` is needed)\n- API designed around Penzai conventions, not Feedbax conventions\n\n### Option B: Implement custom selectors\n\nAs described in the original issue (~250-400 lines).\n\n**Pros**:\n- No external dependency\n- Can tailor API to Feedbax idioms (e.g., integrate with `Graph` surgery)\n- Learn the internals\n\n**Cons**:\n- Implementation and maintenance burden\n- Risk of subtle bugs in tree manipulation\n\n### Option C: Hybrid\n\nUse Penzai selectors initially; if we find the API doesn't fit Feedbax workflows, implement a tailored version later informed by real usage patterns.\n\n---\n\n**Recommendation**: Start with Option A or C. The selector mechanism is non-trivial (boundary marking, keypath tracking, nested selection handling), and Penzai's implementation is solid. We can always wrap or extend it if needed.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","files":null}]}